# bareai

CLI + TUI for solo AI engineers doing AIOps on one bare-metal box.

## Product

- **Name:** `bareai` (binary / package name)
- **Persona:** solo engineer on a single machine (SSH / local)
- **UX:** kubectl-like subcommands **and** interactive TUI (Bubble Tea)
- **Mode:** inspect / probe by default; confirm-gated mutate via `bareai do` only (Docker-scoped)
- **Allowed probes:** status reads, discovery, health checks, one-hit LLM smoke tests
- **Platforms:** macOS, Linux, Windows
- **GPUs:** NVIDIA, AMD, Apple Silicon (degrade gracefully when absent)
- **Runtimes:** Ollama, vLLM, SGLang, Triton, and similar via discovery + HTTP probes
- **Also:** host CPU/RAM/disk, Docker images/containers/volumes, local databases, correlated snapshot

## Stack

- **Language:** Go
- **CLI:** Cobra (or Fang) for commands
- **TUI:** Charm (Bubble Tea + Bubbles + Lip Gloss)
- **Release:** GoReleaser → Homebrew, winget, `.deb` + APT repo (Cloudsmith/Fury)

## Principles

1. Degrade, don't die — missing GPU/Docker/LLM still useful
2. Correlate — join host ↔ GPU ↔ container ↔ model/endpoint ↔ database; every collector feeds `Correlations` or skips
3. Machine-readable — every command supports `--json` for scripts/agents
4. Read-mostly — mutate only through `bareai do` with confirmation; MCP stays read-only
5. Single static binary — no runtime Python/Node dependency

## Out of scope (for now)

Multi-host fleet, mutating ops, Kubernetes-first workflows, official distro packages beyond our own APT/brew/winget.
